^ PHONEIX 3D (FUTURE TALES/ACP&TCP)
-----------------------------------
(50 MHZ 68030/8MB RAM/CD-ROM)

    Bu ay demosunu tan¡tt¡ð¡m Shadow Of 3rd Moon'un demosunu
 oynad¡ktan sonra art¡k AMIGA'da her tµrlµ texture-map 3D
 oyunun yap¡labileceðine inanm¡ß durumday¡m.Phoenix 3D
 AMIGA'da yeni bir ak¡m baßlatabilecek bir oyun...

 @{"> PHOENIX 3D RES¦M #1  " system "ram:ppshow ah16_3:p/14  >NIL:"}

 PC'deki Privateer 1-2 ve Wing Commander 4'µ san¡r¡m hepiniz
 biliyorsunuzdur.Evet Phoenix tahmin ettiðiniz gibi bu oyunlara
 benzer bir oyun.Firma Phoenix'in oynanabilirlik aç¡s¡ndan
 Privateer'a daha çok benzediðini søylµyorlar.

 @{"> PHEONIX 3D RES¦M #2  " system "ram:ppshow ah16_3:p/15  >NIL:"}

 Oyundaki uzaydaki boßlukta geçen 3 boyutlu uzay savaßlar¡
 tamamen 256 renk texture-map grafiklerden olußacak.Pheonix
 yaln¡zca arcade bølµmlerden olußmuyor,yine 256 renk tamamen
 render edilmiß resimlerle sµslenmiß adventure bølµmlerinde
 çeßitli uzayl¡ ¡rklar ile iletißim kuracaks¡n¡z.

 CD'de Aral¡k ay¡ ortalar¡nda piyasaya sµrµlecek oyunda ayr¡ca
 øzel olarak bestelenmiß bir beste bulunacak...

 Oyunun ¦ngilizce olarak detaylar¡ aßað¡da;


PHOENIX is a cocktail of realtime-3D-dogfight, adventure and trading simulation.

Basically  it`s  some  kind  of WingCommander with elements of ELITE, but with a
strong,    linear  storyline  which  is  set  in  4  different  star-systems.<p>
PHOENIX  has  been created and and designed by Emmanuel Henné, a computer artist
who already contributed to TRAPPED! and Hollywood Pictures.

To  create an Amiga game smiliar to Origin`s PRIVATEER saga is his dream, and to
push the AGA-chipset to it`s limit is the goal.

The   programming   part   is  directed  by  3-D-topace  Markus  Poellmann,  who
demonstrated  his  programming  abilities  with  upcoming racing sensation FLIYN
HIGH.

The  epic  soundtrack  will  be  directed  and composed by Markus Castren, who`s
coming right from the demo-scene to contribute to a real game.

PHOENIX`s  3-D-engine  is based on the latest, hottest chunky-to-planar-routines
and  pushes  the  AGA  chipset  to  it`s  limits  by  offering  a fully textured
polygon-engine.

Expect highly detailed starships like You`ve never seen before on a native Amiga
screen,  together  with colourfull backgrounds consisting of clouds, planets and
suns.

These  suns  are  not  just  ordinary  bitmaps,  they are lightsources that will
produce  the  popular lenseflares in realtime, when You take a look at Your ship
from the outside ! 
You  will discover small, agile hunters, big, slow cargo freighters and gigantic
space stations.

The adventure part:

In  the  adventure-story, You`ll fly to exotic places at the border of the known
galaxy.  You`ll encount strange and bizarre aliens, but even more strange humans
You  can  talk  to!  PHOENIX`s    adventure   part  offers of course 256 colours
throughout.   Most   of  the  graphics    have  been  raytraced  on  a  powerful
Blizzard1260-equipped  Amiga1200 with 16  MB fastram. The fantastic environments
and  animations  have  been  designed  and raytraced with CINEMA 4D, the popular
semi-professional 3-D-package.

Other  graphics  have been drawn with the godfather of paintprograms, the famous
and  traditional  Deluxe  Paint V. They were first scribbled in grayscales, then
colourised  in  Ham-8 plus 24-bit, then refined with the outstanding Photogenics
24-bit-image  processor  and  finally colour-reduced with the brilliant Personal
Paint  !  Yes, we are proud to say that the complete artwork of PHOENIX has been
developed exclusively with Amiga hard- and software ! 

256  throughout  state-of-the-art  3-D-engine  raytraced  stills  and animations
Adventure,  Action  and  Trading  based  on  a  linear  storyline many different
characters  more  than  15  planets  to  fly  to more than 15 goods to deal with
TCP/IP-support (planned) 2 years of development 

Hardware requirements

A1200/4000, 68030/50 Mhz or better 4 MB RAM
Harddisk/CD-Drive


Supported

better processor (68040-68060) for better 3-D-performance Graphicscard Multisync
monitor more RAM 

^ FOUNDATION (SADENESS SOFTWARE)
--------------------------------
(68030/4MB/RAM+CD-ROM)

    Programc¡ Paul Burkey taraf¡ndan 2 y¡ld¡r gelißtirilen bu Settlers 2 tarz¡
strateji oyunu art¡k bµtµn Avrupa'da ¦ngiliz Sadeness Software taraf¡ndan
piyasaya sµrµlecek.Bu çok gµzel oyunun ßu anda %80'i bitmiß durumda.Oyunun
tam øzellikleri aßað¡da;

 @{"> FOUNDATION'DAN B¦R RES¦M  " system "ram:ppshow ah16_3:p/3 hi lace >NIL:"}

 Foundation Game Specs

 * ECS,AGA and CyberGFX screen modes with 64, 128 or 256 colours.
 * The game will fully support Graphics cards,  and possibly Sound cards using
AHI too!
 * A standard A1200 with 4Meg fast ram will run the game at full speed in lowres
mode (256 colours).
 * The game will run with 1 Meg of Chipram and at least 1 Meg of any other type
of memory (Fast Ram recomended).
 * CD-ROM is the first format planned to be released. Floppy versions under
consideration.
 * Choice of screen modes including Lowres PAL, NTSC, Hires/Laced, DblPAL etc.
 * Any Screen size from from 320x200 up to 800x600 and beyond!
 * One player Vs. one, two or three computer opponents.
 * Two player split screen mode Vs. one or two computer opponents.
 * Many One player missions and tutorial games.
 * Special Two Player missions.
 * Serial links and TCP/IP support is planned.
 * Custom game setup with different sized maps, enemies, startup modes,
missions.
 * A variety of languages should be supported - including English, German,
Spanish, French and Italian etc.
 * Help-Bubbles may be available to make the game and interface very easy to
use.
 * The CDROM version is planned to feature a custom made intro of over 700
frames!
 * Special Hi-Res graphics may be available for Graphics card users.
 * At least 50Meg of graphics.
 * At least 50Meg of speech samples and sound effects.

 Other Gameplay Features

 Get instant info about any of your people such as:
 * Name -- currently holds 250,000 names.
 * Destination.
 * Health, Morale, Age.
 * Home Building.
 * Place of work.
 * His/Her Comments.
 * What he/she is Carrying.
 * plus much more...

 Order any of your people to...
 * Go Home.
 * Go back to main base.
 * Attack a Building, Person or object.
 * Alter his destination.
 * Stand guard.
 * Rob, loot, steal.
 * Many more commands...

 Features added 2 June 97 include...
 * get a listing of people in any building and give them orders like:-
 * Leave building
 * Do something useful.
 * Take a rest in Hospital (If you have one).
 * Return to Headquarters.
 * The shadow/Dark area system has been totally rewriten. It's not as nice    
as it used to be but it's a hell of a lot faster and it even speeds up     the
game when theres no shadow areas at all. I will try to implement     an option
so you can have the old slow system or the new fast system.
 
 Features added 9 June 97 include...

 * Added a feature to get a detailed listing of a buildings occupants giving    
the occupants names, health and rank. From this list you can now issue    
commands such as Leave, Visit Hospital, Return to HQ. This feature finally    
gives you the full control over the people no matter where they are.
 * Started work on the online help bubble system and also the language support  
  using standard language catalogs.
 * Added new Menu and options screens and rewritten some of the code ready    
for different textures (summer, winter etc..).
 * Added a feature to automatically choose a recommended building when you    
pull up the choose building panel so when you choose a location close     to the
sea it might bring up the pump house or fishery as a default.
 * Started work on the TCP/IP server. Some of the game code has been    
rewritten with "network modes" in mind.
 * Fixed and tweaked many features as well as adding lots of new things     here
and there. The game is running faster and some of the graphics     have been
improved.

 Even more interesting Features!

 * Very unique/quick building methods using the Wizards to create buildings
using magic.
 * Magic is created from cremated corpses which may require some in the name of
progress killing.
 * Many different buildings to be invented and upgraded during play.
 * Almost every feature in the game can be researched/improved.
 * Advanced war strategies with full control over units.
 * Control of units works in a similar way to C&C or WarCraft using a select and
command system.
 * Enemy buildings and people can be stolen and buildimgs can be looted/torched.
 * Diseases/Viruses/Spells can be created, cured, discovered, cast.
 * Not all Characters of each type are the same, they change with age,
experience etc.
 * Find out who were the last four characters to die and the reasons.
 * Maiden and Peasants living in the same building will reproduce.
 * Full control over the amount of workers, resources and people in every
building.
 * It's possible to select 30 or more knights and send them in to attack 1
building or person.
 * Inventions/ideas can be stolen from your enemy.
 * Set up trades with other players and buy/sell resources from stock market.
 * Choose from a complex food chain system or a simple (but expensive/slower)
Food factory system.

